quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  46,6,"When such people are gathered, they will become their enemies and will reject their worship."
  46,7,"When Our clear verses are recited to them, those who disbelieve say about the truth when it comes to them, “This is clear magic.”"
  46,8,"Or do they say, “He has fabricated it”? Say, “If I did fabricate it, there is nothing you can do to protect me against Allah. He knows best that in which you indulge. He is Sufficient as a witness between me and you, and He is the All-Forgiving, the Most Merciful.”"
  46,9,"Say, “I am not the first of the messengers, nor do I know what will happen to me or to you. I only follow what is revealed to me, and I am not but a clear warner.”"
  46,10,"Say, “What do you think, if this [Qur’an] is really from Allah and yet you reject it, and a witness from the Children of Israel has testified in its favor and believed, whereas you persist in arrogance? Indeed, Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people.”"
  46,11,"The disbelievers say about the believers, “If this [faith] were something good, they would not have believed in it before us.” Now since they are not guided by it, they will say, “This is an old fabrication.”"
  46,12,"And before it was the Scripture of Moses a guide and a mercy. This Book is a confirmation of it, in the Arabic language, in order to warn those who do wrong and give glad tidings to those who do good."
  46,13,"Indeed, those who say, “Our Lord is Allah”, then remain steadfast, they will have no fear, nor will they grieve."
  46,14,"They are the people of Paradise; abiding therein forever, as a reward for what they used to do."